        <h4>ABSTRACT</h4>
        <h2>Negotiation for network resources</h2>
        <p>Negotiation for network resources. This patent describes innovations developed by Dr. Tal Lavian in the field of computer networking and data communications.</p>

        <h4>An Inventor: Dr. Tal Lavian</h4>

        <h4>FIELD</h4>
        <h3>Embodiments of the present disclosure are generally related to computer networking and data communications, and in particular to methods and systems for managing, routing, and processing network traffic in packet-switched networks.</h3>

        <h4>BACKGROUND</h4>
        <p>Modern computer networks carry an ever-increasing volume of data traffic, requiring sophisticated management and routing mechanisms. As networks have grown in complexity, the need for efficient packet processing, traffic classification, and quality of service management has become paramount. Network devices must handle diverse traffic types while maintaining performance and reliability.</p>

        <p>Dr. Tal Lavian is a named inventor on this patent, which covers innovations in telecommunications and network communications technology. Dr. Lavian's work spans multiple areas including network architecture, security, interactive communications, frequency synthesis, and autonomous vehicle sensing systems.</p>

        <p>For more details about this patent and Dr. Lavian's extensive patent portfolio, please visit the <a href="/patents/">Patents</a> page or contact Dr. Lavian directly.</p>

